**who —** Golds & Ranks — the twin systems of growth — &quot;Golds,&quot; the currency dropped by enemies and spent in weapon, armor, and magic shops, and the Experience Ranks the Guru bestows as titles when you cross thresholds

**what —** the twin systems of growth — &quot;Golds,&quot; the currency dropped by enemies and spent in weapon, armor, and magic shops, and the Experience Ranks the Guru bestows as titles when you cross thresholds

**where —** FAX · Faxanadu — Hudson Soft, NES 1989 (Famicom 1987; Falcom's Xanadu line)  Framework inputs: Faxanadu; the World Tree; Eolis; the Mantras; the card-keys; Golds & Ranks  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)

**why —** They are the RPG's two ledgers: the purse you spend to grow stronger and the title that says how far you have come — the machinery under the climb.

**how —** Crystallized from Faxanadu (NES 1989) — Famicom Xanadu, on Falcom's licensed Xanadu name.

**◌ the mythos —** They are the RPG's two ledgers: the purse you spend to grow stronger and the title that says how far you have come — the machinery under the climb. a being of the World Tree and the climb to the Evil One

